SRPH-LIT submission is a standard sequence-to-sequence Transformer architecture \cite{vaswani2023attentionneed} combined with ratio-based and embeddings-based data preprocessing \cite{cruz-2023-samsung}, data augmentation via backtranslation \cite{sennrich-etal-2016-improving}, and noisy channel reranking \cite{yee-etal-2019-simple}. We additionally performed a Bayesian hyperparameter search in order to find optimal values for our noisy channel reranking hyperparameters, channel model weight $\delta_{ch}$ and language model weight $\delta_{lm}$. Our system achieves performance that is comparable to Apertium \cite{khanna2021recent} 3.9.6 for Spanish to Asturian translation in terms of BLEU score.

